<br>
I was reading through  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=8449.topic&amp;start=1&amp;stop=20">The Charm 'nerf' and it's faults.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> thread. While I was reading through, Immlazen had a very unique idea. He suggested:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>But I believe once charmed, the Mob should give up alot of attributes. First since they are a pet, they shouldnt be hitting for more then the best pets in the game. Cut there Hitpoints in half...something!!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->When I read this, it sounded similar to how the Necromancer skill &quot;Wake the Dead&quot; works. Thus, I posted this: <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I think this is the most unique thing I've heard as a solution to charm. Let me flesh out a possibility...<br>
<br>
Enchanter_01 charms Mob_01:<br>
<br>
Mob_01, regardless of level, becomes level 60, has 3.5k HP, hits for 85ish, can be controlled, can be hasted/buffed. In short, the Enchanter gains a Magician equivalent pet (in theory the strongest and best pets).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How will this change affect the environment?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
1) Enchanters can utilize charm for what I believe it was meant for, a short term crowd-control ability that adds DPS in a group situation.<br>
<br>
2) Enchanter can also use for soloing, but will drastically eliminate the &quot;Enchanter can outdamage an entire group&quot; problem.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Is this possible?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I don't see why not. The Necro AA &quot;Wake the Dead&quot; already follows this principle. The Necro can &quot;wake&quot; the corpse of a nearby NPC or PC. The pet would then hit for 90s and retain the abilities inherent of the class that is &quot;woken&quot;. The pet has a fixed hit point value along with a fixed level.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>What happens when charm breaks?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Well, a number of things can happen. I suppose the simplest resolution would be to return the previously charmed mob back into an NPC with the abilities inherent of its former self. In terms of HP, perhaps the same percentage of hit points can be given to the mob (since its max HP will be different as an NPC than a Pet).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What do you all think? Would this work? Suggestions? Thoughts?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Note to Enchanters</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: If you do not agree that charm is broken at all, that's fine. This thread is not to discuss whether or not charm is overpowered. This post <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>assumes</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that something needs to be done. This post aims to try and find a fair solution. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60465">Xerphanis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xerphanis>Xerphanis</A> at: 1/16/03 3:23:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izelin>Izelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 3:46:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=449.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Charm solution? (Hopefully not redundant)</span><hr size=1> How do you figure thats fair?  You just wont be happy until you see chanters doing less damage then you huh, thats what your idea is all about.  Figuring out a way for you to get the highest damaging pet...period.    Why would I use charm ever again to get a mob that does a gimp 80 damage when I can DC a mob that does 150 RIGHT NOW?  I can DC a mob in Kael that does 120 + damage.  Theres mobs in POV, HOH, BOT, POS, etc etc which can all be DC'd and do more damage then your idea.  So what you are saying then is dont just nerf charm into an almost useless spell line, but to also nerf our DC as well and make it more gimp then it is just so you can be top dog pet class?  Correct me if im wrong but thats how I read that.  Someone show me where its written that Mages pets are supposed to outdamage chanter charmed pets.  <br>
<br>
Charm isnt going anywhere.  Think outside the box for a minute, theres NOTHING wrong with chanters getting a  pet that outdamage yours...deal with it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maykwhoopee>Mayk Whoopee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 3:48:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=449.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Charm solution? (Hopefully not redundant)</span><hr size=1> With great Rewards (charming a 800-1000dps mob).....comes great Risks (when charm breaks....he knows only your name)...<br>
<br>
Change the charmed mob to the best pet currently in game....and you have moderate (or less) Rewards....for great Risk...<br>
<br>
In short....no one will use it.<br>
<br>
.02<br>
