Doesn't that make you feel like you wasted your time getting DC, when a simple spell can be &gt; DC (dps wise at least). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xerphanis>Xerphanis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 4:04:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=449.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Charm solution? (Hopefully not redundant)</span><hr size=1> Did you folks read my &quot;Note&quot;?<br>
<br>
This is not a discussion of whether or not charm is overpowered. If you think that Charm is perfectly fine as is, that's great. Move on.<br>
<br>
As for comparing the entire Charm spell line to Dire Charm. I don't think you can. The skill, since you spend the points to earn it, is probably fine as it is. However, once you have your DC pet up, you lose the flexibility associated with charm. Also, DC has a level cap, which controls the problem I see in PoP, which are pets with insane DPS. <br>
<br>
From the start, I've always thought of Charm as the ability to crowd control while adding DPS to the group. This spell line is meant to be flexible with some down-side (such as potential death).<br>
<br>
Sure, you're asking now &quot;but charm has a long cast time and high mana cost, why wouldn't I just mez any adds?&quot; That probably should be added to the proposal as well. In order to return Charm to a viable crowd control option, the mana cost needs to be reduce to something similar to Mez with a similar cast time. This way, the option to Charm a mob would be more favorable than Mez, thus making Charm useful again in a group situation NOT just for DPS, but for crowd control.<br>
<br>
Level 64 spell Bliss is a 54 second Mez for 300 mana and mezzes up until level 68 mobs with a 2.5 second cast time.<br>
<br>
